  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dad-\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda-\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca-\u0d91\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1-\u0dba\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca/11-396632",
  "time_ut": 1661512192,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dad \u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d91\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0dba\u0dd9\u0daf\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "An application for remittance of foreign workers",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau and Central Bank of Sri Lanka organized a function to introduce the national mobile app called Lanka Remit among Sri Lankans living abroad. Priority was given here to introduce the facilities and benefits available through the Lanka Remit mobile application to the workers who are preparing to leave for foreign jobs.",
        "Lanka remit mobile app gives Sri Lankans abroad access to send remittances to Sri Lanka faster, safer and more easily.",
        "Foreign workers can remit money to beneficiaries in Sri Lanka through the Lanka remit mobile app, and pay utility bills such as electricity and water bills using foreign-issued e-fund transfer cards. Lanka Remit mobile app also offers many value added services to its users. Accordingly, it is also possible to find information about the nearest registered money transfer service providers and the locations of those money transfer offices through this application.",
        "Lanka remit mobile application can be downloaded from Google play store, Apple app store and Huawei app gallery for anyone sending money to Sri Lanka from any country. Remittance service providers connected to the Lanka Remit mobile application continue to increase, and more service providers in the financial services sector, including global money transfer service providers and global financial innovators, are expected to join the application in the near future to facilitate remittances to Sri Lanka. will",
        "Labor and Foreign Employment Minister Manusha Nanayakkara, Central Bank Governor Dr. Nandalal Weerasinghe, Ministry of Labor and Foreign Employment Secretary R. P. A. Wimalaweera, Vice President of the Bureau A. M. Hilmi and General Manager of the Bureau D. D. Many distinguished guests including Messrs. P. Senanayake attended."
      ],
